p:
Zika virus is a flavivirus spread by 
 Aedes mosquitoes that for >60 years remained only an esoteric threat to human health (

  1
 ). However, the recent Zika epidemic, which erupted in South America in 2015 and became the largest in history, brought the virus to prominence, particularly because infection has been linked to fetal microcephaly and other neurodevelopmental and neurologic sequelae (

  2
 ).
